





	
                
                Parameter Tree:

                
                    EARTH SCIENCE > TERRESTRIAL HYDROSPHERE > SURFACE WATER > RIVERS/STREAMS

                    

                
                Definition:

                
                    River: A large, natural freshwater surface stream having a permanent
or seasonal flow and moving toward a sea, lake, or another river in a
definite channel. Stream: A body of running water moving under the
influence of gravity to lower levels in a narrow, clearly defined natural
channel. 
                
                

                

                
                    Reference:

                    
                        
                            Dictionary of Earth Science, 5th ed. 1997. Sybil Parker, ed. in chief. 
 McGraw-Hill. 
                        
                    
                    

                    

                
            


       







    
    
    
        
    

    
